WEBVTT

00:00.881 --> 00:03.084
DAD, I FEEL LIKE WE NEED TO TALK
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED.

00:03.084 --> 00:04.755
IT WAS AWFUL.

00:04.755 --> 00:07.388
GRAYSON AND I REACHED FOR
THE CREAMER AT THE SAME TIME,

00:07.388 --> 00:10.091
AND FOR JUST A MOMENT,
WE WERE HOLDING HANDS.

00:10.091 --> 00:11.892
I'M TALKING ABOUT
YOU STEALING BOBBY'S BOAT

00:11.892 --> 00:13.804
AND THINKING THAT HE AND I
WERE STILL MARRIED.

00:13.804 --> 00:15.015
WHO'S BOBBY?

00:15.806 --> 00:17.308
GOTCHA!

00:17.308 --> 00:18.809
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:18.809 --> 00:20.401
OH, COME ON, JUNE-BUG.

00:20.401 --> 00:22.443
EVERYBODY FORGETS STUFF
ONCE IN A WHILE, RIGHT?

00:22.443 --> 00:25.276
DAD, FORGETTING
WHO YOUR DAUGHTER IS MARRIED TO

00:25.276 --> 00:26.647
IS NOT A SMALL DETAIL.

00:26.647 --> 00:28.739
SO...THAT'S IT, THEN.

00:28.739 --> 00:32.113
TIME TO WALK ME OUT IN BACK
OF THE BARN AND SHOOT ME.

00:32.113 --> 00:33.204
I UNDERSTAND.

00:33.204 --> 00:34.955
COME ON, DAD.
I'M SERIOUS.

00:34.955 --> 00:37.458
I DON'T LIKE YOU LIVING
AT THAT HUGE RANCH BY YOURSELF.

00:37.458 --> 00:39.210
I WISH YOU LIVED
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD,

00:39.210 --> 00:41.292
SOMEWHERE CLOSE, THAT I COULD
COME VISIT YOU EVERY DAY.

00:41.292 --> 00:43.874
WELL, I SUPPOSE IT WOULD BE NICE
NOT TO HAVE TO KEEP UP

00:43.874 --> 00:45.716
WITH ALL THE WORK
OUT ON THE RANCH.

00:45.716 --> 00:49.670
AND IF I WAS CLOSER,
I COULD COME BY WHENEVER I WANT,

00:49.670 --> 00:51.932
DRINK YOUR BEER
AND PLAY SLAP-A-DOPE.

00:51.932 --> 00:52.933
WHAT'S "SLAP-A-DOPE"?

00:52.933 --> 00:53.634
OHH!

00:53.634 --> 00:55.136
YOU STILL GOT IT.

00:55.136 --> 00:57.848
[ LAUGHS ] I CAN'T BELIEVE
THE DOPE FELL FOR IT.

00:57.848 --> 00:59.810
JOB WELL DONE.
OH, GOOD.

00:59.810 --> 01:01.602
ALL RIGHT, JUNE-BUG.
LET'S DO IT.

01:01.602 --> 01:04.275
START LOOKING FOR A PLACE FOR ME
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

01:04.275 --> 01:05.736
AWW, DAD!
THANK YOU!

01:05.736 --> 01:07.528
OH, THAT MAKES ME
SO HAPPY.

01:07.528 --> 01:09.900
OH, I WISH I KNEW
A REAL-ESTATE AGENT.

01:09.900 --> 01:11.742
BUT I THOUGHT YOU --
GOTCHA!

01:11.742 --> 01:13.574
[ LAUGHS ]

01:13.574 --> 01:15.456
OH, IT'S ONLY FUNNY
WHEN HE DOES IT?

01:15.456 --> 01:20.501
в™Єв™Єв™Є

01:20.501 --> 01:23.294
I CAN'T BELIEVE
TRAV'S COLLEGE GRADUATION

01:23.294 --> 01:24.465
IS THIS WEEKEND.

01:24.465 --> 01:26.006
IF YOU COULD'VE SEEN

01:26.006 --> 01:27.708
THAT DRUNKEN,
HAIR-SPRAYED BEACH TRASH

01:27.708 --> 01:30.711
AND THE DIP-SPITTING MULLET HEAD
WHO CONCEIVED THAT KID,

01:30.711 --> 01:32.513
YOU WOULD NEVER
HAVE EXPECTED THIS.

01:32.513 --> 01:33.674
WHICH ONE WERE YOU?

01:33.674 --> 01:34.975
I DON'T REMEMBER.
[ LAUGHS ]

01:34.975 --> 01:36.557
OKAY, ARE WE ALL SET
FOR THE CEREMONY?

01:36.557 --> 01:38.679
YES, I'VE GOT THE TISSUES,
THE CAMERA,

01:38.679 --> 01:41.101
AND I'M GONNA BE WALKING
WITH GIANT CRUTCHES

01:41.101 --> 01:43.434
THAT ARE ACTUALLY
HOLLOWED-OUT WINE FLASKS.

01:43.434 --> 01:45.356
THAT WAY,
WE GET PRIORITY SEATING

01:45.356 --> 01:47.318
AND A NICE
AFTERNOON BUZZ.

01:47.318 --> 01:50.321
LAURIE, I DON'T THINK I'VE EVER
SAID THIS AND MEANT IT, BUT...

01:50.321 --> 01:51.402
WHAT-WHAT!

01:51.402 --> 01:54.405
THIS IS GONNA BE
SO MUCH FUN!

01:54.405 --> 01:55.656
WHAT'S GONNA BE FUN?

01:55.656 --> 01:57.238
OH, TRAV'S
GRADUATION CEREMONY.

01:57.238 --> 01:59.500
WHAT'S THE STORY?
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO?

01:59.500 --> 02:01.582
NOTHING. WE'RE GOOD.

02:01.582 --> 02:02.953
YEAH.

02:02.953 --> 02:05.456
SO, I GUESS I'LL JUST BE
AT THE, UH, BAR...

02:05.456 --> 02:06.707
IF YOU NEED ME.

02:06.707 --> 02:08.459
SEE YA.

02:08.459 --> 02:11.512
HEY, WILL YOU LOOK OVER
THESE SKETCHES FOR TRAV'S CAKE?

02:11.512 --> 02:13.133
OH, WHAT IS THIS ONE?

02:13.133 --> 02:14.965
IS THIS YOU KISSING
TRAV'S ROLLED-UP DIPLOMA?

02:14.965 --> 02:16.517
NO, THAT'S --
THAT'S A WEIRD DOODLE.

02:16.517 --> 02:18.469
I-I DON'T KNOW
HOW THAT GOT IN THERE.

02:18.469 --> 02:22.263
SO, TRAV, GRADUATION CEREMONY
IS THIS WEEKEND.

02:22.263 --> 02:23.814
PRETTY EXCITING.
YEP.

02:23.814 --> 02:25.436
WHAT I'M REALLY EXCITED FOR

02:25.436 --> 02:27.768
IS SEEING WHAT GIFT
MY DAD GIVES ME.

02:27.768 --> 02:29.440
WELL, IT'S GONNA BE HARD
TO BEAT THE PAST GIFTS.

02:29.440 --> 02:31.612
FOR YOUR PRESCHOOL
GRADUATION,

02:31.612 --> 02:35.115
HE BUILT THE SEWER LAIR FROM
"TEENAGE MUTANT NINJA TURTLES"

02:35.115 --> 02:36.697
IN OUR ACTUAL SEWER.

02:36.697 --> 02:38.118
WE PLAYED NINJA TURTLES
FOR THREE HOURS

02:38.118 --> 02:39.490
AND GOT SICK
FOR FIVE MONTHS.

02:39.490 --> 02:40.661
TOTALLY WORTH IT.

02:40.661 --> 02:42.333
AND THEN,
FOR ELEMENTARY SCHOOL,

02:42.333 --> 02:44.455
YOU TOOK ME
TO MY FIRST PRO-WRESTLING MATCH.

02:44.455 --> 02:46.837
WE SAW CAPTAIN CARNAGE
WIN THE TITLE.

02:46.837 --> 02:49.210
THE WORLD CHAMPION OF
WESTERN CENTRAL FLORIDA, BABY.

02:49.210 --> 02:51.001
THAT'S A BIG AREA!

02:51.001 --> 02:53.714
THAT MATCH IS STILL ONE OF
MY FAVORITE CHILDHOOD MEMORIES.

02:53.714 --> 02:55.676
AND FOR YOUR HIGH SCHOOL
GRADUATION,

02:55.676 --> 02:58.429
HE GOT A 70-FOOT INFLATABLE
GORILLA WITH YOUR FACE ON IT.

02:58.429 --> 02:59.600
HOW DO YOU TOP THAT?

02:59.600 --> 03:01.222
[ CHUCKLES ]
JUST YOU WAIT, BUBBAROO.

03:01.222 --> 03:03.474
THIS WILL BE
THE MOST EPIC GIFT EVER.

03:03.474 --> 03:05.185
WELL, I GOT TO
GET BACK TO WORK.

03:05.185 --> 03:07.147
BUT I CAN'T WAIT
TO HAVE MY MIND BLOWN.

03:07.147 --> 03:08.569
OH, IT'S GONNA BE
BLOWN TO PIECES, BABY!

03:08.569 --> 03:11.982
AND THOSE PIECES
INTO SMALLER PIECES! WHOO!

03:11.982 --> 03:13.484
YOU DON'T HAVE ANYTHING,
DO YOU?

03:13.484 --> 03:15.316
I MEAN, HOW DO YOU TOP
A 70-FOOT INFLATABLE GORILLA?

03:15.316 --> 03:17.238
YOU CAN'T. I'M SCREWED.

03:17.238 --> 03:19.580
I FINALLY CONVINCE MY DAD
TO MOVE CLOSER,

03:19.580 --> 03:22.703
AND I CAN'T FIND A SINGLE HOUSE
THAT'S GONNA WORK FOR HIM.

03:22.703 --> 03:24.495
SOME OF THESE
RETIREMENT COMMUNITIES ARE OKAY,

03:24.495 --> 03:26.247
BUT I DON'T KNOW.

03:26.247 --> 03:29.039
WELL, THAT ONE LOOKS NICE,
AND LOOK ALL THE ACTIVITIES --

03:29.039 --> 03:30.921
SPINNING, WATER AEROBICS,
NAUTILUS.

03:30.921 --> 03:33.384
I WOULD BE IN SUCH KILLER SHAPE
IF I LIVED THERE.

03:33.384 --> 03:35.466
I JUST DON'T KNOW
IF THIS FEELS RIGHT FOR MY DAD.

03:35.466 --> 03:37.718
I MEAN, I DON'T KNOW --
HE'S ALWAYS BEEN SO INDEPENDENT,

03:37.718 --> 03:39.640
AND I DON'T WANT
TO TAKE THAT AWAY FROM HIM.

03:39.640 --> 03:40.931
YEAH, LOOK,
IT'LL WORK OUT.

03:40.931 --> 03:42.433
YOU KNOW,
MAYBE A GREAT NEW HOUSE

03:42.433 --> 03:44.054
WILL COME ON THE MARKET
OR SOMETHING.

03:44.054 --> 03:46.056
OR MAYBE THERE'S EVEN
A CONVERSATION TO BE HAD

03:46.056 --> 03:47.688
ABOUT YOUR DAD
COMING TO LIVE WITH US.

03:48.849 --> 03:50.811
RETIREMENT COMMUNITIES,
HUH?

03:50.811 --> 03:53.484
I HAD MY FIRST "ENCOUNTER"
AT ONE OF THOSE.

03:53.484 --> 03:55.406
I WAS IN MED SCHOOL,
VOLUNTEERING,

03:55.406 --> 03:58.118
AND MARTHA WAS HAVING
HER RETIREMENT PARTY.

03:58.118 --> 03:59.490
TOOK ME BY THE HAND,

03:59.490 --> 04:01.412
LED ME OUT
TO THE SHUFFLEBOARD COURT.

04:01.412 --> 04:02.823
LET'S JUST RUN.

04:05.456 --> 04:07.167
HEY, ELLIE.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

04:07.167 --> 04:10.711
UM, I'M JUST SEEING IF JULES
WANTED TO GRAB SOME LUNCH.

04:10.711 --> 04:12.002
ARE THOSE THE, UH,

04:12.002 --> 04:14.335
GRADUATION DESIGNS
FOR TRAV'S CAKE?

04:14.335 --> 04:15.676
YEAH.

04:15.676 --> 04:17.338
I WANTED TO DO
A GIANT CAKE OF HIS FACE,

04:17.338 --> 04:19.550
BUT I COULDN'T FIGURE OUT HOW
TO GET HIS DIMPLED CHIN RIGHT.

04:19.550 --> 04:20.841
[ GASPS ]
WAIT A MINUTE!

04:20.841 --> 04:22.513
I'VE DONE
BABY-SHOWER CAKES BEFORE.

04:22.513 --> 04:24.014
I CAN USE
MY BABY BUTT MOLD!

04:24.014 --> 04:27.097
IT IS AMAZING TO WATCH
A TRUE ARTIST AT WORK.

04:27.097 --> 04:29.019
YOU'RE LIKE
MICHELANGELO.

04:29.019 --> 04:31.312
MNH. I THINK YOU MEAN
"MIKEY ANGELO,"

04:31.312 --> 04:32.893
THE GUY FROM PIZZA PALACE.

04:32.893 --> 04:34.355
BUT THAT GUY IS A HACK.

04:34.355 --> 04:36.236
YEAH,
GOAT CHEESE ON PIZZA?

04:36.236 --> 04:37.568
IT'S NOT 1985,

04:37.568 --> 04:39.490
AND YOUR NAME'S
NOT WOLFGANG PUCK.

04:39.490 --> 04:42.162
SO, UH, YOU AND JULES
SEEM PRETTY BUSY

04:42.162 --> 04:43.954
WITH THIS
GRADUATION STUFF.

04:43.954 --> 04:45.826
YEAH, IT'S BEEN PRETTY CRAZY,
BUT A LOT OF FUN.

04:45.826 --> 04:47.077
SHE AND I ARE --

04:47.077 --> 04:48.869
WAIT A MINUTE.

04:48.869 --> 04:50.791
YOU FEEL LEFT OUT.

04:50.791 --> 04:52.963
TRAV'S GRADUATION
IS SUCH A BIG DEAL FOR JULES,

04:52.963 --> 04:55.005
BUT YOU'RE
ON THE SIDELINES.

04:55.005 --> 04:57.468
HAVE I PASSED YOU
AS JULES' BEST FRIEND?

04:57.468 --> 04:58.759
OH, PLEASE.

04:58.759 --> 05:00.300
JULES AND I
HAVE BEEN BEST FRIENDS

05:00.300 --> 05:02.182
FOR A MILLION YEARS.

05:02.182 --> 05:05.426
SHE CUT STAN'S UMBILICAL CORD
WHEN ANDY PASSED OUT.

05:05.426 --> 05:08.389
AND WHEN SHE AND I KISS,
WE KISS ON THE LIPS.

05:08.389 --> 05:10.060
OH. MM. OKAY.

05:10.060 --> 05:12.312
LAURIE, WE FORGOT TO SCHEDULE
OUR MANIs AND PEDIs.

05:12.312 --> 05:14.194
WE'LL NEVER GET AN APPOINTMENT
THIS LATE.

05:14.194 --> 05:17.027
WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING
I THOUGHT AHEAD AND BOOKED US

05:17.027 --> 05:18.699
[Singsong voice]
A SPA DAY!

05:18.699 --> 05:21.362
LAURIE, YOU'RE THE BEST!
I LOVE YOU!

05:22.783 --> 05:23.704
MMM.
MMM.

05:23.704 --> 05:24.445
OH!

05:24.445 --> 05:25.446
HEY, ELLIE.

05:25.446 --> 05:26.827
HI.

05:28.999 --> 05:31.372
CHICK.
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU...

05:31.372 --> 05:33.213
WITH SUITCASES,
MOVING BOXES,

05:33.213 --> 05:36.216
AND A...GROCERY BAG
FULL OF HARD CANDIES?

05:36.216 --> 05:37.508
Jules: SURPRISE!

05:37.508 --> 05:39.089
WE DID IT!

05:39.089 --> 05:40.961
I TOLD DAD WHAT YOU SAID
ABOUT HIM MOVING IN,

05:40.961 --> 05:42.222
AND HE SAID YES!

05:42.222 --> 05:43.464
WHAT?

05:43.464 --> 05:44.925
TO SHOW MY GRATITUDE,

05:44.925 --> 05:46.847
I WILL ALLOW YOU
TO HUG ME.

05:47.848 --> 05:50.521
AWW, HE'S JUST SHY!
GET IN THERE, HONEY!

05:50.521 --> 05:52.232
OH, YEAH,
THERE YOU GO!

05:54.435 --> 05:56.567
COME ON,
YOU DUMB SON OF A BITCH.

05:56.567 --> 05:58.439
THE SHOW'S BEEN ON
FOR 30 YEARS.

05:58.439 --> 06:01.241
ANSWER IN THE FORM
OF A QUESTION!

06:01.241 --> 06:03.864
[ CHUCKLES ]
HOW AMAZING IS THIS?

06:03.864 --> 06:05.195
IT'S PERFECT!

06:05.195 --> 06:07.408
YEAH, I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT PERFECT, BUT...

06:07.408 --> 06:08.489
OF COURSE IT IS!

06:08.489 --> 06:10.330
AND IT WAS ALL
YOUR IDEA.

06:10.330 --> 06:11.792
JUNE-BUG!

06:11.792 --> 06:12.753
YEAH?

06:12.753 --> 06:15.546
WHERE SHOULD I HANG MOLLY?

06:18.088 --> 06:21.672
DID YOU KNOW SOME OLDER MEN'S
NOSES WHISTLE CONSTANTLY?

06:21.672 --> 06:24.505
AROUND THE CLOCK, NEVER STOP.
WHY IS THAT?

06:24.505 --> 06:27.307
I THINK IT'S JUST
NORMAL WEAR AND TEAR,
LIKE BRAKES ON A CAR.

06:27.307 --> 06:28.679
AND I DON'T NEED TO KNOW

06:28.679 --> 06:30.390
WHEN A GUY'S HEADED
TO THE BATHROOM, OKAY?

06:30.390 --> 06:31.432
BE DISCREET.

06:31.432 --> 06:32.773
DON'T MAKE A BIG SHOW

06:32.773 --> 06:34.314
OF PUTTING A NEWSPAPER
UNDER YOUR ARM

06:34.314 --> 06:35.776
AND SAYING
"ANCHORS AWAY."

06:36.777 --> 06:38.068
HEY, EVERYBODY.

06:38.068 --> 06:41.021
LOOK WHO IT IS --
SECOND PLACE.

06:41.021 --> 06:42.573
THE SILVER MEDAL.

06:42.573 --> 06:45.826
JULES' BEST FRIEND, PART 2:
ELECTRIC BOOGALOO.

06:45.826 --> 06:49.079
YOU FOUND THE ONE WAY
TO SURPASS ME --

06:49.079 --> 06:50.871
BY COZYING UP TO TRAV

06:50.871 --> 06:54.294
AND BANGING YOUR WAY
UP THE FRIEND LADDER.

06:55.456 --> 06:56.957
YO, YO, YO, YO.

06:56.957 --> 06:59.590
I SHOULD HAVE BANGED YOU
YEARS AGO!
SAY WHAT?

06:59.590 --> 07:01.421
HI. I'M YOUR HUSBAND.
HAVE WE MET?

07:01.421 --> 07:03.423
I COULD STILL DO IT,
YOU KNOW.

07:03.423 --> 07:05.756
SEDUCE TRAV,
STEAL HIM AWAY FROM YOU,

07:05.756 --> 07:09.640
AND THEN I COULD JUST HUMP
MY WAY BACK INTO FIRST PLACE.

07:09.640 --> 07:11.261
TRAV, COME HERE.

07:11.261 --> 07:13.684
LET ME SHOW YOU
HOW A REAL WOMAN MAKES OUT.

07:14.685 --> 07:16.396
CAN I GET
A SHOT AND A BEER?

07:16.396 --> 07:18.228
WHEN AN OLDER GUY
BLOWS HIS NOSE,

07:18.228 --> 07:19.770
IT'S LIKE AN AIR HORN.

07:19.770 --> 07:22.062
AND HOW MANY TIMES
DO YOU GET TO USE A HANDKERCHIEF

07:22.062 --> 07:23.484
BEFORE YOU HAVE TO WASH IT?

07:23.484 --> 07:25.275
I'M LEAVING.

07:25.275 --> 07:26.487
TRAV.

07:26.487 --> 07:29.910
YOU KNOW WHERE I'LL BE,
DON'T YOU?

07:31.161 --> 07:33.574
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

07:33.574 --> 07:35.455
BYE, NUMBER 2!

07:35.455 --> 07:36.837
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ON TV ]

07:36.837 --> 07:39.129
OH, CHICK.
YOU'RE UP.

07:39.129 --> 07:42.382
SO I DIDN'T IMAGINE
ALL THOSE FARTS AND SNEEZES.

07:42.382 --> 07:44.044
YEAH, I'M ALWAYS UP.

07:44.044 --> 07:45.756
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

07:45.756 --> 07:48.298
OH, SOMETIMES WHEN I NEED
A LITTLE ALONE TIME,

07:48.298 --> 07:50.350
I'LL POP DOWN HERE
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT,

07:50.350 --> 07:52.302
JUST ME AND MY GUITAR --
QUIET.

07:52.302 --> 07:54.094
ALONE.

07:54.094 --> 07:55.395
[ EXPLOSION ]
BOOM!

07:55.395 --> 07:58.478
TAKE THAT,
YOU NAZI BASTARDS.

07:58.478 --> 08:00.811
REALLY LOVING
THE HISTORY CHANNEL, HUH?

08:00.811 --> 08:04.605
I'M WATCHING WORLD WAR II's
GREATEST EXPLOSIONS.

08:04.605 --> 08:08.739
NEXT PROGRAM IS GONNA REVEAL
WHO REALLY KILLED JFK.

08:08.739 --> 08:11.241
LEE HARVEY OSWALD?
ACTING ALONE?

08:11.241 --> 08:14.665
THAT MIGHT BE THE STUPIDEST
DAMN THING I EVER HEARD.

08:14.665 --> 08:15.916
Jules: HEY!

08:15.916 --> 08:17.668
LATE-NIGHT HANG SESH?

08:17.668 --> 08:20.581
[ GASPS ]
MAKE ROOM FOR J-BIRD!

08:20.581 --> 08:22.883
Grayson: WELL, I ACTUALLY
JUST CAME DOWN HERE TO PLAY

08:22.883 --> 08:24.294
A LITTLE GUITAR.

08:24.294 --> 08:25.626
[ EXPLOSION ]

08:25.626 --> 08:27.427
[ GASPS ]
TAKE THAT, YOU NAZI BASTARDS!

08:27.427 --> 08:29.509
ALLIED FORCES RULE!

08:29.509 --> 08:30.841
OH, YEAH!

08:30.841 --> 08:32.472
I'LL BE OUT IN THE SHED.

08:32.472 --> 08:35.596
DAD, NEXT, THEY'RE GONNA TELL US
WHO REALLY KILLED JFK.

08:35.596 --> 08:39.690
GRAYSON THINKS IT WAS OSWALD --
ACTING ALONE.

08:39.690 --> 08:40.731
OH, BOY.

08:40.731 --> 08:41.852
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

08:41.852 --> 08:43.944
OH, MY GOSH!
THAT'S SO STUPID!

08:43.944 --> 08:47.487
HEIGH-HO, SILVER MEDAL.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

08:47.487 --> 08:49.319
IT'S 9:00 A.M.
YOU'RE NEVER UP THIS EARLY.

08:49.319 --> 08:51.652
JUST HAD A COFFEE CRAVING.
THAT'S ALL.

08:51.652 --> 08:54.034
WHY ARE YOU WEARING
THAT SWEATER?

08:54.034 --> 08:55.415
IT'S NOT COLD OUT.

08:55.415 --> 08:57.497
WAIT A MINUTE.

08:57.497 --> 08:59.620
THAT'S JULES'
FAVORITE SWEATER ON YOU.

08:59.620 --> 09:01.922
IT'S THE ONE SHE SAYS
MAKES YOUR BOOBS POP.

09:01.922 --> 09:04.424
JULES LIKES THIS SWEATER?
I DID NOT REALIZE.

09:04.424 --> 09:07.087
I AM JUST WEARING IT
'CAUSE IT'S SO COMFY COZY.

09:07.087 --> 09:10.761
YOU'RE TRYING TO SCORE
JULES POINTS, AREN'T YOU?

09:10.761 --> 09:12.432
I'M NOT.
I'M JUST HAVING --

09:12.432 --> 09:13.553
COOL IT, NUMBER 2!

09:13.553 --> 09:15.055
I'M JULES' BFF.

09:15.055 --> 09:17.307
A STATEMENT THAT
IF PUT TO SONG AND DANCE

09:17.307 --> 09:18.849
WOULD SOUND
SOMETHING LIKE THIS.

09:18.849 --> 09:20.851
в™Є I'M JULES' BFF! в™Є

09:20.851 --> 09:22.482
в™Є I'M JULES' BFF! в™Є

09:22.482 --> 09:24.484
в™Є I'M JULES' BFF! в™Є

09:24.484 --> 09:26.276
в™Є I'M JULES' BFF! в™Є

09:26.276 --> 09:27.397
в™Є I'M JULES' BF-- в™Є

09:30.490 --> 09:33.493
MAN, WE HAD SO MANY GREAT IDEAS
FOR TRAV'S GIFT.

09:33.493 --> 09:35.746
I CAN'T BELIEVE THEY ALL
TURNED OUT TO BE IMPRACTICAL.

09:35.746 --> 09:38.408
AHH, THE MONKEY-FILLED CLOWN CAR
WAS GENIUS.

09:38.408 --> 09:41.291
WHO KNEW IT'D BE SO HARD TO GET
30 MONKEYS ON SHORT NOTICE?

09:41.291 --> 09:43.003
WELL, WE CAN'T MISS
WITH THIS IDEA.

09:43.003 --> 09:45.335
JUST GET A CRAPLOAD OF FIREWORKS
AND LIGHT UP THAT CEREMONY

09:45.335 --> 09:46.837
LIKE IT WAS
"INDEPENDENCE DAY" --

09:46.837 --> 09:48.508
THE MOVIE,
NOT THE HOLIDAY.

09:48.508 --> 09:50.050
HI, GUYS.
HOW YOU DOING?

09:50.050 --> 09:52.132
YOU GOT ANYTHING THAT WE CAN
SHOOT UP INTO THE SKY

09:52.132 --> 09:54.014
AND SPELL OUT
"CONGRATULATIONS, TRAVIS.

09:54.014 --> 09:56.096
WE'RE ALL SO PROUD OF YOU.
WAY TO GO, BUDDY"?

09:56.096 --> 09:57.638
UH, NO.

09:57.638 --> 09:59.770
BUT THIS ONE SPINS ON THE GROUND
WHEN YOU LIGHT IT.

09:59.770 --> 10:02.643
YEAH, THAT'S NOT GONNA WORK.
WE NEED SOMETHING WITH MORE POP.

10:02.643 --> 10:04.604
WE LITERALLY WANT
TO BLOW PEOPLE'S SOCKS OFF.

10:04.604 --> 10:06.146
WE NEED TO SEE
THE ILLEGAL STASH.

10:12.733 --> 10:14.695
WE'LL TAKE ALL OF IT!

10:17.497 --> 10:20.330
STOLEN POLICE BADGE, HUH?
HOW MUCH?

10:20.330 --> 10:23.003
OH, MAN! YOU TRY TO UP-SELL US
WITH THE HANDCUFFS.

10:23.003 --> 10:24.454
THAT'S HOW
THEY ALWAYS GET YOU.

10:24.454 --> 10:26.296
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ON TV ]

10:26.296 --> 10:28.508
OH. NOW YOU'RE ALL INTO
THE HISTORY CHANNEL, TOO?

10:28.508 --> 10:31.421
THE ALLIES ARE KICKING
SOME SERIOUS ASS TODAY.

10:31.421 --> 10:33.964
YOU KNOW, IF YOU REALLY THINK
ABOUT THE JFK ASSASSINATION --

10:33.964 --> 10:37.017
I DON'T HAVE TO.
IT WAS OSWALD.

10:37.017 --> 10:38.098
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

10:38.098 --> 10:39.349
NOTHING.

10:39.349 --> 10:41.061
IT'S JUST
THAT THE HOUSE NOW --

10:41.061 --> 10:44.644
IT ALWAYS SMELLS LIKE
LIVER AND ONIONS AND CIGARS,

10:44.644 --> 10:46.146
AND THE HEAT'S
TURNED UP TO 90,

10:46.146 --> 10:48.108
AND THE VOLUME'S ALL THE WAY UP
ON THE TV,

10:48.108 --> 10:49.690
AND CHICK'S
ALWAYS YELLING AT IT.

10:49.690 --> 10:51.031
YEAH,
HE IS A CHARACTER.

10:51.031 --> 10:52.773
NO, HE'S ANNOYING!

10:52.773 --> 10:54.775
AND WHY DOES HE ALWAYS
HAVE TO USE OUR BATHROOM?

10:54.775 --> 10:56.486
'CAUSE HE SAYS
THE SOFTER SEAT HELPS HIM

10:56.486 --> 10:57.657
WITH THE STRAIN
OF HIS --

10:57.657 --> 10:59.990
STOP! STOP.
I DON'T -- UGH.

10:59.990 --> 11:01.661
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU'RE SO UPSET.

11:01.661 --> 11:03.283
I MEAN, YES,
MY DAD CAN BE A HANDFUL,

11:03.283 --> 11:05.125
BUT YOU STILL WANTED HIM
TO MOVE IN WITH US.

11:05.125 --> 11:07.127
NO! I DIDN'T!

11:07.127 --> 11:09.499
I SAID WE COULD DISCUSS IT,
AND THEN WE DIDN'T.

11:09.499 --> 11:11.341
YOU JUST WENT
AND MADE IT HAPPEN,

11:11.341 --> 11:13.794
AND NOW HE'S HERE,
AND IF I DON'T PUT UP WITH IT,

11:13.794 --> 11:15.796
I'M SUDDENLY THE BAD GUY!

11:17.297 --> 11:19.139
EXACTLY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:19.139 --> 11:21.681
NOW I AM.
I'M -- I'M THE BAD GUY.

11:23.764 --> 11:25.766
[ TOILET FLUSHES ]

11:25.766 --> 11:27.107
JULES!

11:27.107 --> 11:28.809
DAD, I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE IN THERE.

11:28.809 --> 11:30.150
DID YOU JUST HEAR
ALL THAT?

11:30.150 --> 11:31.401
YEAH. I HEARD.

11:31.401 --> 11:32.813
WHERE'S THE PLUNGER?

11:35.695 --> 11:38.118
DAD, I'M SO SORRY
YOU HAD TO HEAR ALL THAT.

11:38.118 --> 11:40.120
GRAYSON DIDN'T MEAN
WHAT HE SAID.

11:40.120 --> 11:41.742
HE COMPLAINS
ALL THE TIME.

11:41.742 --> 11:44.875
I MEAN, TO BE HONEST,
HE'S KIND OF A LITTLE BITCH.

11:44.875 --> 11:46.286
PLEASE DON'T BE UPSET.

11:46.286 --> 11:48.999
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.
I GOT A THICK SKIN.

11:48.999 --> 11:51.631
BUT I DON'T WANT YOU
TO FEEL UNWELCOME.

11:51.631 --> 11:53.794
I MEAN,
WE BOTH WANT YOU HERE.

11:53.794 --> 11:56.176
JULES, IF YOUR HUSBAND
WANTS ME HERE,

11:56.176 --> 11:57.798
HE'S OUT OF HIS DAMN MIND.

11:58.718 --> 12:02.803
YOUR MOM'S DAD --
YOUR GRANDPA MARTY --

12:02.803 --> 12:04.684
HE CAME TO STAY WITH US
FOR A WHILE

12:04.684 --> 12:06.266
WHEN YOU WERE
A LITTLE GIRL.

12:06.266 --> 12:07.727
OH, YEAH.

12:07.727 --> 12:09.729
HE USED TO SIT
ON THE FRONT PORCH IN HIS BOXERS

12:09.729 --> 12:12.272
AND EAT PICKLES
AND...CURSE AT BIRDS.

12:12.272 --> 12:14.815
MARTY WAS NOT
A BRIGHT MAN.

12:14.815 --> 12:18.448
BUT HAVING HIM THERE WITH US
MADE YOUR MOM HAPPY,

12:18.448 --> 12:22.452
AND I LOVED HER SO MUCH,
IT WAS WORTH IT.

12:22.452 --> 12:24.244
YOU WERE A GREAT HUSBAND.

12:24.244 --> 12:25.916
SO IS GRAYSON.

12:25.916 --> 12:29.539
THAT'S WHY HE'S MAKING AN EFFORT
TO PUT UP WITH ME --

12:29.539 --> 12:31.171
BECAUSE HE LOVES YOU.

12:31.171 --> 12:33.423
HE'S PRETTY AMAZING,
ISN'T HE?

12:33.423 --> 12:35.836
DURING THE TIME
I'VE BEEN HERE WITH YOU,

12:35.836 --> 12:37.217
HAVE YOU TOLD HIM THAT?

12:41.141 --> 12:43.974
WELL, WELL, WELL.
LOOK WHO IT IS.

12:43.974 --> 12:45.265
CAKEZILLA.

12:45.265 --> 12:47.017
LAURIE,
I'M SO, SO SORRY.

12:47.017 --> 12:49.689
I SHOULD NOT HAVE SMASHED
YOUR CAKE.

12:49.689 --> 12:51.441
WHY DID YOU FREAK OUT
LIKE THAT?

12:51.441 --> 12:53.273
I WAS JUST GIVING YOU
A HARD TIME.

12:53.273 --> 12:55.695
I DIDN'T EXPECT YOU TO GO
ALL SILVERBACK ON ME.

12:55.695 --> 12:58.899
I KNOW. I JUST THINK
YOU TOUCHED ON A SORE SPOT.

12:58.899 --> 13:00.570
I'M ACTUALLY NOT BOTHERED

13:00.570 --> 13:02.492
THAT YOU AND JULES
HAVE BECOME CLOSER.

13:02.492 --> 13:04.454
I JUST FEEL LIKE
SHE HAS SO MANY THINGS

13:04.454 --> 13:06.036
GOING ON IN HER LIFE
RIGHT NOW

13:06.036 --> 13:08.578
THAT I'M NOT A PRIORITY
TO HER.

13:08.578 --> 13:11.461
WHAT -- ARE YOU CRAZY?
YOU'RE ALWAYS A PRIORITY.

13:11.461 --> 13:13.874
SERIOUSLY, IT GOES
"WINE, TRAVIS, YOU."

13:13.874 --> 13:15.966
AND SOMETIME, WHEN TRAVIS
IS BEING REALLY ANNOYING

13:15.966 --> 13:17.587
ABOUT SOME BORING
PHOTOGRAPHY THING,

13:17.587 --> 13:20.260
I SWEAR
IT'S "WINE, YOU, TRAVIS."

13:20.260 --> 13:21.801
HE CAN BE
AN IRRITATING NERD.

13:21.801 --> 13:24.594
AND EVEN IF IT SOMETIMES
SEEMS LIKE

13:24.594 --> 13:26.556
I MIGHT HAVE PASSED YOU
ON JULES' LIST,

13:26.556 --> 13:28.688
IT'S ONLY BECAUSE
I'M SLEEPING WITH HER SON.

13:28.688 --> 13:30.270
AND THAT'S BASICALLY
CHEATING.

13:30.270 --> 13:31.731
THAT'S TRUE.

13:31.731 --> 13:34.354
I EARNED MY SPOT,
AND YOU SLUTTED YOUR WAY IN.

13:34.354 --> 13:36.066
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:36.066 --> 13:37.607
THANK YOU, LAURIE.

13:37.607 --> 13:40.280
I'M SORRY
IF IT WAS SO MUCH TO CLEAN UP.

13:40.280 --> 13:42.362
CLEAN IT UP? NO, HONEY,
I LEFT RIGHT AFTER YOU DID.

13:42.362 --> 13:44.654
SO WE JUST LEFT HER KITCHEN
COVERED IN CAKE?

13:44.654 --> 13:45.996
[ GASPS ]

13:45.996 --> 13:47.117
SHOULD WE BLAME BOBBY?

13:47.117 --> 13:48.618
YES. DONE.
YEAH. OKAY.

13:48.618 --> 13:50.620
LET'S GET YOU SOME WINE.
PLEASE.

13:50.620 --> 13:53.083
MAN, I CAN'T BELIEVE
WE GOT ARRESTED.

13:53.083 --> 13:54.915
UNDERCOVER 5-0, MAN.

13:54.915 --> 13:57.958
SO, TRAV'S GRADUATING TOMORROW,
AND I STILL GOT NOTHING.

13:57.958 --> 14:00.010
WELL, MAYBE YOU'RE
APPROACHING THIS WRONG.

14:00.010 --> 14:01.631
WHAT'S GRADUATION ABOUT,
REALLY?

14:01.631 --> 14:04.384
GOING TO A PARTY
AND FINALLY TELLING

14:04.384 --> 14:06.346
THAT REALLY CUTE GIRL
FROM YOUR PSYCH CLASS

14:06.346 --> 14:08.768
THAT YOU LOVE HER AND WOULD DO
ANYTHING TO BE WITH HER

14:08.768 --> 14:10.810
AND LAUGHING
AND PRETENDING IT WAS ALL A JOKE

14:10.810 --> 14:13.313
WHEN HER MUSCULAR
SWEDISH BOYFRIEND WALKS UP?

14:13.313 --> 14:16.526
ON THE SURFACE, SURE,
BUT IT'S ALSO A MILESTONE --

14:16.526 --> 14:18.858
A TIME TO CONSIDER
NOT JUST WHERE YOU'RE GOING,

14:18.858 --> 14:19.980
BUT WHERE YOU'VE BEEN.

14:19.980 --> 14:22.402
IT'S TREASURED MEMORIES --

14:22.402 --> 14:25.695
BIRTHDAY PARTIES,
LITTLE LEAGUE GAMES,

14:25.695 --> 14:27.787
YOUR FIRST KISS,

14:27.787 --> 14:31.661
THE TASTE OF GRAPE BUBBLE GUM
ON CINDY LLEWELLYN'S LIPS.

14:32.752 --> 14:34.874
IT'S NOSTALGIA.

14:36.957 --> 14:39.129
I KNOW WHAT TO GET TRAV!
CAPTAIN CARNAGE!

14:39.129 --> 14:42.132
HIS FAVORITE WRESTLER!
HE LIVES HERE IN FLORIDA!

14:42.132 --> 14:43.553
I'M GONNA TRACK
THAT SON OF A BITCH DOWN

14:43.553 --> 14:45.175
AND GET HIM
TO GRADUATION!

14:45.175 --> 14:47.467
RIGHT. I DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME
TO MAKE THIS HAPPEN.

14:47.467 --> 14:50.640
ANDO, I NEED YOU TO KEEP WORKING
ON PLAN "B" IN CASE I FAIL.

14:50.640 --> 14:51.972
I WILL, BOBBY.
I WILL.

14:51.972 --> 14:53.393
W-WHAT DO YOU WANT ME
TO DO?

14:53.393 --> 14:55.565
JUST KEEP BEING BEAUTIFUL,
BABY!

14:55.565 --> 14:56.896
HEY.
OH, HEY! JULES!

14:56.896 --> 14:58.688
HOW'D YOU KNOW
I WAS HERE?

14:58.688 --> 15:00.320
WELL, WHENEVER
WE'RE IN A FIGHT

15:00.320 --> 15:02.232
AND YOU DON'T KNOW
WHO SCREWED UP MORE,

15:02.232 --> 15:04.284
YOU COME HERE,
YOU GET A DOZEN CUPCAKES,

15:04.284 --> 15:07.287
AND YOU DECIDE WHETHER
YOU SHOULD GIVE THEM
TO ME AND APOLOGIZE

15:07.287 --> 15:09.909
OR YOU SHOULD EAT THEM YOURSELF
BECAUSE YOU'RE SO UPSET.

15:09.909 --> 15:13.293
[ SIGHS ]
I WAS SO CONFLICTED.

15:13.293 --> 15:14.794
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:14.794 --> 15:17.627
I'M GONNA HAVE TO DO
SO MANY CRUNCHES.

15:17.627 --> 15:20.670
JULES, I'M REALLY SORRY
I BLEW UP AT YOU.

15:20.670 --> 15:22.172
NO, HONEY.
THIS IS MY FAULT.

15:22.172 --> 15:23.803
I SHOULD HAVE
TALKED TO YOU MORE

15:23.803 --> 15:25.635
BEFORE ASKING DAD
TO MOVE IN WITH US.

15:25.635 --> 15:27.097
I JUST --
I GOT SO EXCITED

15:27.097 --> 15:29.099
AT THE FACT THAT YOU SAID
IT WAS AN OPTION

15:29.099 --> 15:31.681
THAT I STARTED TO REALLY BELIEVE
THAT'S WHAT YOU WANTED.

15:31.681 --> 15:32.892
I WAS BEING SELFISH.

15:32.892 --> 15:34.814
I DO WANT HIM
TO MOVE IN WITH US.

15:34.814 --> 15:36.106
NO, YOU DON'T.

15:36.106 --> 15:37.647
AND YOU SHOULDN'T.
THAT WOULD BE CRAZY.

15:37.647 --> 15:39.439
I MEAN, IT WOULD MAKE ME
SO HAPPY

15:39.439 --> 15:40.900
TO HAVE DAD
LIVE WITH US,

15:40.900 --> 15:42.862
BUT THAT IS NOT
A GOOD ENOUGH REASON.

15:42.862 --> 15:45.365
NO, YOU'RE WRONG.
IT'S THE PERFECT REASON.

15:47.117 --> 15:49.619
JULES, MAKING YOU HAPPY
IS MORE IMPORTANT TO ME

15:49.619 --> 15:51.241
THAN ANYTHING
IN THE WORLD,

15:51.241 --> 15:52.952
SO THAT'S WHY
WE'RE GONNA DO THIS.

15:52.952 --> 15:54.834
THAT'S WHY
HE'S GONNA MOVE IN WITH US.

15:54.834 --> 15:57.287
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU SO MUCH
THAT I J--

15:57.287 --> 15:59.579
MM.

15:59.579 --> 16:01.081
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:01.081 --> 16:02.922
JULES,
PEOPLE ARE WATCHING US.

16:02.922 --> 16:04.584
MM.
I'M SO TURNED ON.

16:04.584 --> 16:06.506
MM. I DON'T CARE.
OH, REALLY?

16:08.348 --> 16:09.929
OH, MY GOD!

16:11.301 --> 16:12.852
ELLIE!

16:12.852 --> 16:15.225
COME OVER HERE SO I CAN SEE
WHAT YOU'RE WEARING TODAY!

16:15.225 --> 16:16.896
YOU CARE WHAT I WEAR?

16:16.896 --> 16:19.689
OF COURSE!
IT'S TRAV'S COLLEGE GRADUATION!

16:19.689 --> 16:22.692
YOU'LL BE STANDING NEXT TO ME
IN EVERY SINGLE PICTURE.

16:22.692 --> 16:24.484
I WILL?
WHO ELSE
WOULD I BE STANDING NEXT TO?

16:24.484 --> 16:25.985
MY HUSBAND?

16:25.985 --> 16:29.279
AND WHEN I GET SO HAPPY
THAT I HAVE TO KISS SOMEONE,

16:29.279 --> 16:31.371
I'M GRABBING YOU.
NOT LAURIE?

16:31.371 --> 16:33.243
NO!
SHE'S WAY TOO AGGRESSIVE.

16:33.243 --> 16:34.824
IT'S LIKE
PUTTING YOUR MOUTH

16:34.824 --> 16:37.327
ON THE NOZZLE
OF A GAS-STATION VACUUM.

16:37.327 --> 16:38.828
I'LL GO GET
MY BEST OUTFIT.

16:38.828 --> 16:40.170
SOMETHING
THAT MAKES YOUR BOOBS POP.

16:40.170 --> 16:41.421
YOU KNOW, LIKE MINE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:41.421 --> 16:43.253
OKAY!

16:43.253 --> 16:45.465
Chick:
WELL, THIS IS NICE,

16:45.465 --> 16:49.219
BEING HERE
FOR MY GRANDSON'S GRADUATION.

16:49.219 --> 16:51.681
TOO BAD HE'S GRADUATING
FROM ART SCHOOL.

16:51.681 --> 16:55.305
I HEAR HIS MACARONI-NECKLACE
FINAL WAS A KILLER.

16:55.305 --> 16:57.847
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:57.847 --> 17:00.980
LOOK, CHICK, UM...
ABOUT WHAT I SAID...

17:00.980 --> 17:04.023
YOU WERE JUST VENTING.

17:04.023 --> 17:07.447
AND YOU HAVE EVERY RIGHT.
I'M NOT AN EASY HOUSEGUEST.

17:07.447 --> 17:09.859
WELL...YEAH.
YOU'RE A HANDFUL.

17:09.859 --> 17:11.281
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:11.281 --> 17:14.864
BUT YOU'RE FAMILY, CHICK.
AND WE CARE ABOUT YOU.

17:14.864 --> 17:16.826
AND I'M GLAD YOU'RE THERE.

17:16.826 --> 17:20.750
YOU'RE A GOOD MAN, GRAYSON.
JULES IS LUCKY TO HAVE YOU.

17:24.334 --> 17:26.336
THE MAFIA
DIDN'T KILL JFK.

17:26.336 --> 17:27.667
DID SO.
DID NOT.

17:27.667 --> 17:29.839
SO, THIS SIDE
IS THE RED ONE.

17:29.839 --> 17:31.971
RIGHT IS RED,
LEFT IS WHITE.

17:31.971 --> 17:33.883
RED IS RIGHT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:33.883 --> 17:35.675
OOH!
HEY.

17:35.675 --> 17:37.477
LAURIE, TAKE A PICTURE
OF ME AND ELLIE.
OKAY.

17:37.477 --> 17:39.099
AND "CHEESE!"

17:39.099 --> 17:41.271
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]
OH, IT'S A GOOD ONE.

17:41.271 --> 17:43.943
I THINK WE SHOULD CALL IT
"BEST FRIENDS FOREVER."

17:43.943 --> 17:45.445
I LIKE IT.

17:45.445 --> 17:46.526
SHE LIKES IT.

17:46.526 --> 17:47.777
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:47.777 --> 17:49.529
THANKS FOR TELLING ME
SHE WAS UPSET.

17:49.529 --> 17:51.451
OF COURSE.
WHAT ARE BEST FRIENDS FOR?

17:51.451 --> 17:53.993
OH, DON'T START.
I'M KIDDING.
COME ON. LET'S GO.

17:53.993 --> 17:55.495
WHEW!

17:55.495 --> 17:57.577
BOBBY! THERE YOU ARE!
THE CEREMONY'S ABOUT TO START!

17:57.577 --> 17:59.199
I'VE BEEN TO TAMPA
AND BACK.

17:59.199 --> 18:00.660
I'VE BEEN IN THREE DIFFERENT
GYMS, FOUR DIFFERENT BARS,

18:00.660 --> 18:02.202
TWO PIGGLY WIGGLYS,
AND AN ALLIGATOR FARM,

18:02.202 --> 18:03.253
BUT I GOT HIM!

18:03.253 --> 18:05.545
CAPTAIN CARNAGE, BABY!

18:05.545 --> 18:07.086
THANKS FOR HAVING ME.

18:07.086 --> 18:09.169
YOU KNOW, I HAVE A REAL RESPECT
FOR EDUCATION.

18:09.169 --> 18:10.260
KNOWLEDGE IS POWER.

18:10.260 --> 18:11.301
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:11.301 --> 18:12.592
THERE'S A SLIGHT PROBLEM.

18:12.592 --> 18:14.214
YOU KNOW,
WHEN I DIDN'T HEAR FROM YOU,

18:14.214 --> 18:16.216
I-I WENT
WITH MY BACKUP PLAN.

18:16.216 --> 18:17.677
WHAT WAS THAT?

18:19.098 --> 18:20.600
BIG DADDY PAYNE.

18:20.600 --> 18:22.722
CARNAGE.
OH, YOU BROUGHT BDP?

18:22.722 --> 18:24.814
HE AND THE CAPTAIN
ARE MORTAL ENEMIES, MAN.

18:24.814 --> 18:26.816
OH. WELL, THEY'RE ACTORS.
IT'S NOT REAL.

18:26.816 --> 18:29.359
HEY, WHAT PART
OF "LOSER LEAVES TOWN"

18:29.359 --> 18:31.491
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND,
BDP?

18:31.491 --> 18:33.112
[ GROWLS ]
UNDERSTAND THIS,
CARNAGE --

18:33.112 --> 18:35.495
I'M GONNA KICK YOUR ASS!

18:35.495 --> 18:36.786
NOT IF I KICK YOURS
FIRST!

18:36.786 --> 18:38.408
WHOA! OH, WHOA!

18:38.408 --> 18:40.740
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

18:40.740 --> 18:43.243
BDP! CARNAGE!
MAN, CHILL OUT!

18:43.243 --> 18:45.295
THEY'RE GONNA RUIN
TRAVIS' GRADUATION!

18:45.295 --> 18:47.207
THEN WE HAVE TO STOP THEM.

18:47.207 --> 18:48.798
YAAGH!
AAAH!

18:48.798 --> 18:51.211
DAD, WHAT --
WHAT'S GOING --

18:51.211 --> 18:52.422
WHOA!

18:52.422 --> 18:54.013
ANDO!

18:54.013 --> 18:56.135
AAAAH!

18:56.135 --> 18:59.219
OH, IT IS ON NOW!
I'M COMING, GUYS!

18:59.219 --> 19:01.851
[ GROWLS ]

19:01.851 --> 19:03.893
GOT THE RIFLE,
AND, YEAH, THAT'S HARD,

19:03.893 --> 19:05.185
BUT I-IT'S ONE GUY.

19:05.185 --> 19:06.436
IT COULD STILL --
IT COULD HAPPEN.

19:06.436 --> 19:08.768
ALL RIGHT!
LET'S DO THI--

19:08.768 --> 19:09.899
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

19:09.899 --> 19:11.771
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

19:11.771 --> 19:13.983
AAAAAAAAH!
OHHHHH!

19:13.983 --> 19:17.407
[ GLASS BREAKING ]
WELL, THIS CEREMONY
JUST GOT SO MUCH BETTER.

19:17.407 --> 19:18.698
AAAAH!

19:18.698 --> 19:20.700
BAAAAAAAAGH!

19:20.700 --> 19:21.951
WHO'S NEXT?!

19:21.951 --> 19:23.743
BDP!

19:23.743 --> 19:24.744
[ GROWLS ]

19:24.744 --> 19:26.456
IS THAT BIG DADDY PAYNE?

19:26.456 --> 19:29.289
HE ONCE SIGNED MY BOOBS
AT AN AUTO SHOW.

19:29.289 --> 19:31.551
I SAW A LOT OF THESE BRAWLS
WHEN I WAS A KID.

19:31.551 --> 19:33.673
USUALLY, MY MOM WENT HOME
WITH THE WINNER.

19:33.673 --> 19:35.004
YOU TWO
ARE SUCH WHITE TRASH.

19:35.004 --> 19:36.296
THAT'S NOT WHAT I --

19:36.296 --> 19:38.468
I MEAN,
SOMEBODY WENT TO OSWALD.

19:38.468 --> 19:40.720
AAAH! AAH!

19:40.720 --> 19:42.011
[ ALL GASP ]

19:43.803 --> 19:46.185
[ WRESTLERS GRUNTING ]

19:46.185 --> 19:47.767
DID YOU DO THIS?

19:47.767 --> 19:49.859
I JUST WANTED TO GIVE YOU
AN AWESOME GRADUATION PRESENT.

19:49.859 --> 19:50.900
I'M SO SORRY.

19:50.900 --> 19:51.941
SORRY FOR WHAT?

19:51.941 --> 19:54.023
THIS IS AMAZING!

19:54.023 --> 19:55.315
IT IS?
YES!

19:55.315 --> 19:57.156
YOU TRACKED DOWN
MY FAVORITE WRESTLERS!

19:57.156 --> 19:59.909
I GOT TO SEE MY DAD TAKE A CHAIR
TO CAPTAIN CARNAGE'S FACE!

20:01.030 --> 20:02.912
THIS IS YOUR MOST IMPRESSIVE
GIFT YET.

20:02.912 --> 20:04.203
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:04.203 --> 20:05.995
WHAT?!
I GOTTA GET BACK IN THERE, SON.

20:05.995 --> 20:07.457
HAPPY GRADUATION!

20:07.457 --> 20:08.498
WHOO!

20:09.499 --> 20:11.791
AAAAAAAH! AAH!

20:11.791 --> 20:12.792
WHOO!

20:14.594 --> 20:16.796
WHEW! THAT WAS
AN EPIC RUMBLE.

20:16.796 --> 20:18.298
A REAL SLOBBERKNOCKER.

20:18.298 --> 20:20.219
CAPTAIN CARNAGE BIT ME.

20:20.219 --> 20:22.802
HE BLEW A CLOUD OF CHILI POWDER
IN MY FACE.

20:22.802 --> 20:24.434
HOW DID HE HAVE CHILI POWDER
ON HIM?

20:24.434 --> 20:26.846
WAS HE ANTICIPATING A BRAWL,
OR DOES HE JUST WALK AROUND

20:26.846 --> 20:28.728
WITH CHILI POWDER
IN HIS POCKET?

20:29.729 --> 20:32.231
WE'RE FORMING A THREE-MAN
PRO-WRESTLING TAG TEAM,

20:32.231 --> 20:33.653
AREN'T WE?

20:33.653 --> 20:36.526
WE'LL CALL OURSELVES
THE FLYING DANDIES.

20:36.526 --> 20:38.738
I'M GONNA WEAR A LION'S HEAD
AROUND MY REGULAR HEAD,

20:38.738 --> 20:41.361
AND I'M GONNA HAIL
FROM THE PARTS UNKNOWN!

20:41.361 --> 20:43.783
I'M GONNA GET A SHIV
AND STAB CAPTAIN CARNAGE.

20:43.783 --> 20:45.535
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

20:49.789 --> 20:51.291
WAS HE TALKING ABOUT
OUR WRESTLING TEAM,

20:51.291 --> 20:54.213
OR IS HE ACTUALLY GONNA GO STAB
CAPTAIN CARNAGE?

20:54.213 --> 20:55.335
TOM?!

20:55.335 --> 20:57.337
TOM! TOM!
